---
import { Activity, ArrowRight, ClipboardCheck, FlaskConical, HeartHandshake, Moon, TestTubes } from '@lucide/astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';

const coreSymptoms = [
  {
    title: 'Reduced capacity and profound fatigue',
    text: 'A substantial reduction in the ability to complete usual activities, lasting more than six months and accompanied by fatigue that is not relieved by rest.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Post-exertional malaise',
    text: 'A delayed worsening of symptoms after physical, cognitive, emotional or social activity that was previously tolerated.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Unrefreshing sleep',
    text: 'Sleep that does not restore energy or function, even when the duration appears adequate.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Cognitive or upright symptoms',
    text: 'Difficulty thinking or concentrating, orthostatic intolerance, or both.'
  }
];

const assessmentAreas = [
  {
    title: 'General laboratory assessment',
    text: 'A blood count, ferritin and iron studies, vitamin B12, folate, glucose, electrolytes, kidney and liver markers may be useful depending on what has already been assessed.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Thyroid assessment',
    text: 'TSH is usually the starting test. Free T4, thyroid antibodies or other markers may be added when symptoms, history or previous results provide a reason.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Sleep and autonomic symptoms',
    text: 'Unrefreshing sleep, sleep apnea symptoms, dizziness, palpitations and difficulty remaining upright may require focused assessment or referral.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Medication and nutrition review',
    text: 'Medications, restrictive diets, gastrointestinal symptoms and supplement use can all affect fatigue, nutrient status or sleep.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="ME/CFS Care and Assessment | Halifax"
  description="Patient-centred ME/CFS care in Halifax with pacing, symptom management, assessment for overlapping conditions and selected supportive services."
  focusKeyword="chronic fatigue syndrome treatment Halifax"
>
  <HeroSection
    title="ME/CFS and Chronic Fatigue"
    compact
    image={{ src: '/images/conditions/chronic-fatigue-hero.webp', alt: 'Person resting while living with persistent fatigue', aspect: 'video' }}
  >
    <p>Myalgic encephalomyelitis/chronic fatigue syndrome is a serious, complex illness in which symptoms can worsen substantially after even modest activity.</p>
    <p class="text-white/80">Care centres on respecting energy limits, managing the most disruptive symptoms and assessing other conditions that may be adding to the fatigue.</p>
    <CTAButton slot="cta" source="me-cfs-hero" />
  </HeroSection>

  <section class="bg-white py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Understanding the condition</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 sm:text-4xl">ME/CFS is more than persistent tiredness</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          <p>
            ME/CFS affects multiple body systems and can substantially limit work, school, household tasks and social activity. Its defining feature is <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800">post-exertional malaise (PEM)</strong>: a worsening of symptoms after activity that may begin hours or days later and last for days or longer.
          </p>
          <p>
            There is no single laboratory test that confirms ME/CFS. Diagnosis is based on the pattern, duration and severity of symptoms, together with an assessment for other explanations. There is currently no cure or treatment that works reliably for everyone, but individual symptoms and overlapping conditions can often be managed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          {coreSymptoms.map(({ title, text }) => (
            <article class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50 p-6">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-emerald-950">{title}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">{text}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-emerald-950 py-16 text-white lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-emerald-400/15 text-emerald-300">
            <Activity class="h-6 w-6" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4 mt-6 text-emerald-300">Protecting against symptom crashes</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium !text-white sm:text-4xl">Pacing is a central part of ME/CFS management</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/75">
            Pacing means balancing activity and rest so that physical, cognitive, emotional and social demands remain within your current limits. It is not a fixed exercise program and it does not mean pushing through symptoms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl !text-white">Recognize patterns</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-white/70">A brief activity-and-symptom record can help identify delayed crashes and less obvious forms of exertion.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl !text-white">Plan before symptoms rise</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-white/70">Break tasks into smaller parts, alternate demanding and restorative activities, and include rest proactively.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl !text-white">Include mental exertion</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-white/70">Conversation, screens, concentration, noise and emotional stress can all use limited energy.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl !text-white">Adjust as capacity changes</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-white/70">Energy limits can fluctuate. The plan should respond to the patient’s present capacity rather than a predetermined progression.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-[#f7f7f5] py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-4">A practical clinical approach</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 sm:text-4xl">Care is built around the symptoms affecting you most</h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">The plan begins with what is most disruptive and what can be addressed safely, without assuming that every symptom has one underlying cause.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
          <ClipboardCheck class="h-7 w-7 text-emerald-700" aria-hidden="true" />
          <h3 class="mt-5 font-serif text-2xl text-emerald-950">Clarify the symptom pattern</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Review onset, PEM, sleep, pain, cognition, upright symptoms, infections, medications and the investigations already completed.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
          <TestTubes class="h-7 w-7 text-emerald-700" aria-hidden="true" />
          <h3 class="mt-5 font-serif text-2xl text-emerald-950">Assess treatable contributors</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Testing is selected to look for anemia, nutrient deficiencies, thyroid disease, metabolic issues or other conditions that can coexist with ME/CFS.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
          <HeartHandshake class="h-7 w-7 text-emerald-700" aria-hidden="true" />
          <h3 class="mt-5 font-serif text-2xl text-emerald-950">Choose manageable supports</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">Prioritize pacing and the most troublesome symptoms, then consider nutrition or other supportive services when the expected benefit justifies the effort and cost.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] lg:items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Laboratory assessment</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 sm:text-4xl">Testing looks for conditions that may overlap with ME/CFS</h2>
          <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            Laboratory testing does not diagnose ME/CFS. It can, however, help identify a separate or additional problem that has a specific treatment. The selection should reflect your symptoms, history and previous results rather than a fixed panel ordered for everyone.
          </p>
          <a href="/lab-testing/" class="mt-7 inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-emerald-700 hover:text-emerald-900">
            Explore laboratory testing <ArrowRight class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" />
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          {assessmentAreas.map(({ title, text }) => (
            <article class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50 p-6">
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-emerald-950">{title}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">{text}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-emerald-50 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr] lg:items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-white text-emerald-800 shadow-sm">
            <FlaskConical class="h-6 w-6" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4 mt-6">IV nutrient therapy</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 sm:text-4xl">An optional service for selected patients—not a cure for ME/CFS</h2>
          <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            <p>
              IV nutrient therapy delivers vitamins and minerals directly into the bloodstream. It is used in the practice for selected patients after clinical screening, particularly when there is a clear nutritional or clinical reason to consider an intravenous route.
            </p>
            <p>
              Evidence that IV nutrient mixtures improve ME/CFS itself is limited. Treatment is therefore individualized, with the expected benefit, demands of attending the clinic, cost and potential risks discussed before proceeding. It should not replace pacing, medical assessment or treatment of an identified condition.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a href="/iv-therapy/" class="mt-7 inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-emerald-700 hover:text-emerald-900">
            Learn about IV therapy <ArrowRight class="h-4 w-4" aria-hidden="true" />
          </a>
        </div>

        <aside class="rounded-3xl border border-emerald-100 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-10">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-emerald-950">What the published evidence shows</h3>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
            <p>
              A 2002 paper described the author’s clinical experience using a Myers’ Cocktail for several conditions, including fatigue. It was not a controlled ME/CFS trial.<sup>1</sup>
            </p>
            <p>
              A systematic review found limited signals for NADH and magnesium, but the underlying studies used oral NADH and injected magnesium—not a Myers’ Cocktail or an IV ME/CFS protocol. The reviewers could not draw firm conclusions because the studies were small and at high risk of bias.<sup>2</sup>
            </p>
            <p>
              A small controlled Myers’ Cocktail study involved people with fibromyalgia, not ME/CFS. Outcomes improved in both the treatment and placebo groups, with no statistically significant difference between them.<sup>3</sup>
            </p>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <div class="grid gap-8 rounded-3xl border border-emerald-100 bg-[#f7f7f5] p-8 sm:p-10 lg:grid-cols-[auto_1fr]">
          <div class="inline-flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800">
            <Moon class="h-7 w-7" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950">Symptom management remains important</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
              Sleep problems, pain, headaches, dizziness, gastrointestinal symptoms and mood changes can each deserve focused attention. Addressing one symptom may make daily life more manageable even when it does not change the underlying ME/CFS. Referrals or coordination with other healthcare providers are recommended when appropriate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQSection items={[
    {
      question: 'Is there a cure for ME/CFS?',
      answer: '<p>There is currently no cure or approved treatment that reliably resolves ME/CFS. Care focuses on preventing post-exertional crashes, managing the most disruptive symptoms and treating any separate conditions found during assessment.</p>'
    },
    {
      question: 'Can blood testing diagnose ME/CFS?',
      answer: '<p>No. ME/CFS is diagnosed from the clinical pattern and after considering other explanations. Blood work can identify conditions such as anemia, iron or vitamin B12 deficiency, thyroid disease, diabetes, liver or kidney problems that may cause or add to fatigue.</p>'
    },
    {
      question: 'Should I exercise to build my energy?',
      answer: '<p>Standard exercise programs can worsen post-exertional malaise. Activity should stay within your current limits and be adjusted according to symptoms. Pacing is individualized and does not require steadily increasing activity.</p>'
    },
    {
      question: 'Is IV nutrient therapy required?',
      answer: '<p>No. IV nutrient therapy is optional and is not a cure for ME/CFS. It is used in the practice for selected patients after screening and a discussion of the evidence, expected benefit, effort, cost and risks.</p>'
    },
    {
      question: 'What if I also have long COVID?',
      answer: '<p>Long COVID and ME/CFS can share symptoms, including post-exertional malaise. The history, timing and full symptom pattern should be reviewed carefully. Pacing may be important, while other symptoms or complications may require assessment through your broader healthcare team.</p>'
    }
  ]} />

  <section class="bg-emerald-950 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-medium !text-white sm:text-4xl">Discuss your fatigue and current limits</h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/80">Book a consultation to review your symptom pattern, previous investigations and the most manageable next steps.</p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <CTAButton source="me-cfs-final" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-12 lg:py-16">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl border-t border-slate-200 pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-slate-700">Selected references</h2>
        <ol class="mt-5 list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
          <li>Gaby AR. Intravenous nutrient therapy: the “Myers’ cocktail.” <em>Altern Med Rev</em>. 2002;7(5):389–403.</li>
          <li>Alraek T, Lee MS, Choi TY, Cao H, Liu J. Complementary and alternative medicine for patients with chronic fatigue syndrome: a systematic review. <em>BMC Complement Altern Med</em>. 2011;11:87.</li>
          <li>Ali A, Njike VY, Northrup V, et al. Intravenous micronutrient therapy for fibromyalgia: a placebo-controlled pilot study. <em>J Altern Complement Med</em>. 2009;15(3):247–257.</li>
          <li>Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. Manage ME/CFS: treatment and symptom management guidance. Updated May 2024.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
